column1: #Text=Tarrlok says : " A few years later , my father taught us to bloodbend anytime , without the need of the full moon .
#Text=That 's what you need to strive for .
#Text=" Tarrlok says : " Even though Noatak was my father 's favorite , it was n't any easier for him .
#Text=He carried the burden of all Yakone 's expectations and demands .
#Text=Something changed in Noatak over the years ; the loving brother I once knew became cold and detached .
#Text=Our father pushed us to extremes , and one day , he made us bloodbend each other .
#Text=" Yakone says : " Bloodbend your brother , Tarrlok !
#Text=I do n't want to do that to anyone .
#Text=" Yakone says : " You 're a disgrace , a weakling .
#Text=I 'll teach you a lesson , you insubordinate - " Noatak says : " Stay away from him .
#Text=" Yakone says : " How dare you bloodbend me !
#Text=" Noatak says : " What 're you gon na do about it ?
#Text=You always say bloodbending is the most powerful thing in the world , but it is n't .
#Text=What could be more powerful than that ?
#Text=" Yakone says : " I made you what you are .
#Text=" Noatak says : " We 're your sons , not your tools of revenge .
#Text=" Noatak says : " He was right about you .
